topic.title: Need some advice on 0site
topic.body:
http://127.0.0.1:43110/1HHZVBPikyCaPZ69P1QgYbT3UpKa6jvLFV/rf/files.html

I'm wanting to share file here. however this section can grow large in size.  We know we can set optional files however  we do not leave this computer running for log period of times (Old hardware).  So some less popular file might not get distributed. 

Even going to the above link does it download the files for you?,  Just want to test that part of the site is working..?

I know large 0Site don't normally do well...

Would a good alternative be to upload the file to mega and share them from there? even if they get wiped from mega we still would have the file to upload, or put on the site as optional. Or does some one know of a better service?

Thoughts?

topic.title: RF we are still alive
topic.body:
YES! we are still alive. had an automation script go wrong and deleted and published the site. But it has been restored.

http://127.0.0.1:43110/1HHZVBPikyCaPZ69P1QgYbT3UpKa6jvLFV/#Meta

We have uploaded files to mega to save space on the site, while this is not
ideal. It will do for now. If some one has any tips to store large files, external
to zeronet email us below.

In this update we have added More ODs so check them out.

If you have any suggestions for the site let us know here: roguefiles@zeroid.bit

Also post below if the site is working for you, to let us know if everything is in good shape.
